  "prompt": "What's that device on umpire's arm?",
  "response": "The device on an umpire's arm is typically a communication system, often referred to as a \"radio earpiece\" or \"communication headset.\" This allows the umpire to communicate discreetly with other officials, such as the crew chief or other umpires, during a game. In some sports, it may also be used to receive information from a replay official or to communicate with the game's management. The device helps ensure that the officials can stay in sync and make decisions efficiently.",
